    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Four- to 6-inch planes with the front edge open so that the iron can cut at the very nose of the plane; used for trimming in hard to reach places.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000036401/Salaman, Dictionary of Tools Used in Woodworking (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schaven van ongeveer 10 tot 15 centimeter lang, waarvan de voorkant open is zodat de beitel helemaal vooraan de schaaf kan schaven. Worden gebruikt om moeilijk bereikbare plekken bij te schaven.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052490/Clason, Elsevier tools and ironware (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>4至6英吋長的刨子，其前緣有開口，可鉋片在槽鉋最前端便開始切削；用以盡量修整邊緣地帶。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
